<title>FRANCE: Rexel buys three businesses, sells one.</title>
<headline>Rexel buys three businesses, sells one.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-03-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Rexel, a subsidiary of French retailer Pinault-Printemps-Redoute, said on Friday it had acquired ABB's wholesale electrical equipment business, which had 400 million francs of annual sales.</p>
<p>It said in a statement that in late 1996, it bought Boehm &amp; Hennes, with 50 million francs in sales, and Britain's Sunbridge, with 70 million francs in sales.</p>
<p>It has also signed an agreement to sell Omnitech Sertronique, with 107 million francs in sales, to Britain's Eurodis Electron Plc. The sale should close on April 17.</p>
<p>Rexel did not disclose the terms of the deals.</p>
